snippet.textDisplay: Ole may have a plan to build for the future, but you can see he is still green. SAF would sometimes buy players ready made just to keep us in touch with Glory. Because when you've forgotten what it feels like for too long you fall into the category of teams that nearly had what it takes to make it to the next step. Like Liverpool has been until now or Arsenal or Spurs. I remember when City became a force to reckon. SAF pulled the impossible to land the Dutch maestro RVP. He delivered and made sure we stayed in the spot lights. Right now OLE should have an eye on 2-3 veterans that could galvanise these youngsters. For e.g it's no coincidence that Pogba in his first season trained and behaved well. Zlatan was Jose's man behind the scenes to keep egos in check. We need some leaders on and off the pitch. Ole should re-evaluate his assessment and get the players he needs before it's too late!

He delivered and made sure we stayed in the spot lights. Right now OLE should have an eye on 2-3 veterans that could galvanise these youngsters.
